key trends :



Scaling up capacities: Recyclers are expanding processing capacities through opening large automated facilities to handle projected increase in spent EV batteries available for recycling.

Technology development: Investments into R&D around improving lithium extraction efficiencies and recovery rates given the valuable battery raw material. Goal to get closer to near 100% recycling.

Redwood Materials, a major lithium-ion battery recycler raised $775 million signaling massive growth opportunity. Their recycling process claims recovery rates of nickel (98%), cobalt (98%), and lithium (92%).

Partnerships with OEMs: Recyclers forging alliances with EV automakers and battery companies to implement battery collection, logistics infrastructure and ensure access to used pack supply.

Advances in hydrometallurgical and pyrometallurgic recycling processes enabling safer and more sustainable methods vs mining.

Geographic expansion plans driven by policy incentives especially in Europe around EV sustainability.

